1278
01:21:53,280 --> 01:21:55,084
(GUNS COCKING)

1279
01:22:49,080 --> 01:22:50,406
(SCREAMS)
(SHELLS CLATTERING)

1280
01:23:11,120 --> 01:23:12,606
Finish it!

1281
01:23:18,680 --> 01:23:19,961
(GROANS)

1282
01:23:26,800 --> 01:23:28,286
You freak, die!

1283
01:23:37,640 --> 01:23:38,841
(SCREAMING)

1284
01:23:41,800 --> 01:23:43,650
(HEAVY FOOTSTEPS)

1285
01:24:11,440 --> 01:24:13,688
(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

1286
01:24:17,360 --> 01:24:18,846
Watch out.

1287
01:24:18,960 --> 01:24:20,599
LEWIS: Need me to call a doctor?

1288
01:24:20,600 --> 01:24:22,802
Come on, Jack.
You're gonna like this.

1289
01:24:25,320 --> 01:24:26,479
What the hell you doin' here?

1290
01:24:26,480 --> 01:24:27,839
Y'all gonna play good cop, bad cop?

1291
01:24:27,840 --> 01:24:30,771
Nah, Daniels. Bad cop, RoboCop.

1292
01:24:32,520 --> 01:24:35,839
ROBOCOP: I've recovered 26
guns from Vallon's warehouse.

1293
01:24:35,840 --> 01:24:38,799
Thirteen serial numbers match
weapons missing from Evidence.

1294
01:24:38,800 --> 01:24:40,799
And I got your prints all over 'em.

1295
01:24:40,800 --> 01:24:41,959
This is bullshit.

1296
01:24:41,960 --> 01:24:43,839
ROBOCOP: I also have CCTV footage

1297
01:24:43,840 --> 01:24:45,999
of you and Vallon the same
day he tried to kill me.

1298
01:24:46,000 --> 01:24:48,319
<i>VALLON: So put him on the payroll.
Why we talkin' about this?</i>

1299
01:24:48,320 --> 01:24:51,799
<i>DANIELS: It won't work. Now that his partner
got hit, he's never gonna let it go.</i>

1300
01:24:51,800 --> 01:24:53,399
<i>- VALLON: What is that?
- LAKE: Lewis' hospital.</i>

1301
01:24:53,400 --> 01:24:54,999
<i>Murphy's dropping
by this afternoon.</i>

1302
01:24:55,000 --> 01:24:58,039
<i>I kill a cop, I'm lookin'
over my shoulder...</i>

1303
01:24:58,040 --> 01:25:00,561
You know what they do
to cops in prison, man?

1304
01:25:00,800 --> 01:25:03,606
Being locked up with the
same dudes you put in there?

1305
01:25:06,720 --> 01:25:08,649
How long you think
before he gives you up?

1306
01:25:09,080 --> 01:25:10,441
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

1307
01:25:12,200 --> 01:25:15,085
Don't shoot me. Okay?

1308
01:25:15,880 --> 01:25:18,359
I swear to Christ. It was Dean.

1309
01:25:18,360 --> 01:25:21,450
She helped pull those guns.
Just don't shoot me.

1310
01:25:23,200 --> 01:25:25,402
Thank you for your cooperation.

1311
01:25:26,160 --> 01:25:27,319
(SCREAMS)

1312
01:25:27,320 --> 01:25:29,090
You can cuff him now, Jack.

1313
01:25:37,960 --> 01:25:40,049
Now I know why we
couldn't get an arrest.

1314
01:25:41,160 --> 01:25:43,359
'Cause Vallon was protected
from up on high.

1315
01:25:43,360 --> 01:25:45,244
Alex, I can explain.

1316
01:25:45,720 --> 01:25:47,199
You tipped him off today.

1317
01:25:47,200 --> 01:25:48,519
Come on, man. Don't do this.

1318
01:25:48,520 --> 01:25:50,519
You tried to kill me twice.

1319
01:25:50,520 --> 01:25:54,008
I trusted you.
And you destroyed my family.

1320
01:25:54,120 --> 01:25:55,321
Confess.

1321
01:25:56,440 --> 01:25:58,239
Now, in front of everyone.

1322
01:25:58,240 --> 01:25:59,441
Confess!

1323
01:26:03,160 --> 01:26:04,771
(PEOPLE GASP)

1324
01:26:09,080 --> 01:26:10,239
What happened?

1325
01:26:10,240 --> 01:26:12,559
Tin Man is down.
Had to be done.

1326
01:26:12,560 --> 01:26:13,719
<i>Why?</i>

1327
01:26:13,720 --> 01:26:15,039
Product shot a corrupt cop.

1328
01:26:15,040 --> 01:26:16,599
Two more seconds,
the chief's brains

1329
01:26:16,600 --> 01:26:19,280
would've been splattered
across the 6:00 news.

1330
01:26:19,560 --> 01:26:20,799
We got anything on her?

1331
01:26:20,800 --> 01:26:23,239
Well, she's the Chief of the
Detroit Police Department.

1332
01:26:23,240 --> 01:26:25,283
What do you think?

1333
01:26:28,920 --> 01:26:30,451
You know what?

1334
01:26:31,640 --> 01:26:35,083
This might actually tip this
thing right into the net.

1335
01:26:41,320 --> 01:26:44,683
<i>NOVAK ON TV: Alex, I don't
know if you can hear me.</i>

1336
01:26:44,800 --> 01:26:48,239
<i>But tonight, you uncovered
a nest of vipers</i>

1337
01:26:48,240 --> 01:26:50,839
<i>inside the Detroit
Police Department.</i>

1338
01:26:50,840 --> 01:26:55,364
<i>And in so doing, you shed
light on an invaluable truth.</i>

1339
01:26:55,800 --> 01:26:57,319
Even the police,

1340
01:26:57,320 --> 01:27:01,570
the men and women who
swore to keep us safe,

1341
01:27:02,120 --> 01:27:03,845
they can be bribed.

1342
01:27:04,280 --> 01:27:07,324
They can be bought.

1343
01:27:08,760 --> 01:27:13,090
Machines, however,
are corruption free.

1344
01:27:13,840 --> 01:27:16,159
Americans could be
living in a country

1345
01:27:16,160 --> 01:27:19,682
where law enforcement
is not only efficient,

1346
01:27:19,800 --> 01:27:21,525
but incorruptible.

1347
01:27:22,640 --> 01:27:25,119
Thank you, Alex, for
all you've done.

1348
01:27:25,120 --> 01:27:27,049
And for all that you are.

1349
01:27:27,320 --> 01:27:30,683
<i>Detective Murphy is currently
in critical condition.</i>

1350
01:27:31,160 --> 01:27:33,999
Our doctors are working ceaselessly

1351
01:27:34,000 --> 01:27:36,839
but, at this time, it is
unclear if he will survive.

1352
01:27:36,840 --> 01:27:38,039
(REPORTERS CLAMORING)

1353
01:27:38,040 --> 01:27:40,119
<i>KELLY: Ms. Kline, how do
you think the attempt</i>

1354
01:27:40,120 --> 01:27:42,079
<i>on Detective Alex Murphy's life</i>

1355
01:27:42,080 --> 01:27:44,479
<i>will affect tomorrow's
vote for the Dreyfus Act?</i>

1356
01:27:44,480 --> 01:27:46,439
<i>LIZ: At this time,
Omnicorp's sole concern</i>

1357
01:27:46,440 --> 01:27:48,722
<i>is the full recovery
of Detective Murphy.</i>

1358
01:27:49,640 --> 01:27:51,879
<i>How many times does
Detective Murphy</i>

1359
01:27:51,880 --> 01:27:54,526
<i>have to give his life
for his country?</i>

1360
01:27:54,960 --> 01:27:59,919
<i>I sincerely hope the Senate
makes the right vote tomorrow</i>

1361
01:27:59,920 --> 01:28:04,682
<i>so that Alex Murphy's sacrifices
will not have been in vain.</i>

1362
01:28:09,200 --> 01:28:11,519
<i>OHIO SENATOR ON TV:
Senator Dreyfus is my friend.</i>

1363
01:28:11,520 --> 01:28:14,399
<i>He has been my mentor
and my strength</i>

1364
01:28:14,400 --> 01:28:17,080
<i>in times of difficulty
on this floor.</i>

1365
01:28:17,360 --> 01:28:20,559
<i>But despite all that, I
work for the state of Ohio,</i>

1366
01:28:20,560 --> 01:28:23,889
<i>and the safety of its
citizens is my top priority.</i>

1367
01:28:24,040 --> 01:28:25,239
<i>So I vote yes.</i>

1368
01:28:25,240 --> 01:28:27,761
<i>The Dreyfus Act must be repealed.</i>

1369
01:28:27,880 --> 01:28:30,239
That's us ahead, 39 to 10.

1370
01:28:30,240 --> 01:28:33,239
I spoke to the Senate liaison and
it looks like it's in the bag,

1371
01:28:33,240 --> 01:28:36,399
but we still have to tread
carefully with the politicians.

1372
01:28:36,400 --> 01:28:37,879
(NOVAK ELEMENT THEME SONG PLAYING ON TV)

1373
01:28:37,880 --> 01:28:40,239
<i>KELLY: We're here live
at DPD headquarters</i>

1374
01:28:40,240 --> 01:28:43,079
<i>where moments ago, Clara Murphy
made a shocking statement.</i>

1375
01:28:43,080 --> 01:28:44,359
POPE: What the hell?

1376
01:28:44,360 --> 01:28:49,600
<i>Omnicorp has denied me and my
son access to Alex for weeks.</i>

1377
01:28:50,080 --> 01:28:52,123
<i>I demand to know why.</i>

1378
01:28:52,920 --> 01:28:58,126
<i>This treatment is inhuman and somebody
needs to be held accountable.</i>

1379
01:28:59,120 --> 01:29:01,079
Oh, we're fucked.

1380
01:29:01,080 --> 01:29:02,559
No, we only need 12 votes.

1381
01:29:02,560 --> 01:29:04,199
She shouldn't make much difference.

1382
01:29:04,200 --> 01:29:06,519
POPE: Yeah, but what
about after the vote?

1383
01:29:06,520 --> 01:29:08,439
I mean, those two should
not be allowed contact.

1384
01:29:08,440 --> 01:29:10,959
If she starts putting
ideas in his head...

1385
01:29:10,960 --> 01:29:13,799
Bring her in. I'll
handle the explanation.

1386
01:29:13,800 --> 01:29:15,359
POPE: And what about Alex?

1387
01:29:15,360 --> 01:29:17,801
You know, unfortunately,
we can't just keep him on ice.

1388
01:29:18,280 --> 01:29:20,879
LIZ: The shooting at the station
spooked some of the politicians.

1389
01:29:20,880 --> 01:29:23,559
They're our clients.
We have to take care of them.

1390
01:29:23,560 --> 01:29:27,079
They're fine when a machine
is lowering the murder rate,

1391
01:29:27,080 --> 01:29:30,439
but when a man is investigating
city politics, they get nervous.

1392
01:29:30,440 --> 01:29:32,919
All right. First off,
it's not a man, okay?

1393
01:29:32,920 --> 01:29:34,959
It's property of Omnicorp.

1394
01:29:34,960 --> 01:29:37,279
And politics are the
least of your concern.

1395
01:29:37,280 --> 01:29:39,119
I mean, this thing
solved its own murder.

1396
01:29:39,120 --> 01:29:41,599
How long till it realizes you
haven't been on the level with it?

1397
01:29:41,600 --> 01:29:42,799
POPE: If that happens,

1398
01:29:42,800 --> 01:29:45,799
every journalist in this country
is dying to speak to him.

1399
01:29:45,800 --> 01:29:47,968
I mean, we created a hero.

1400
01:29:48,320 --> 01:29:51,171
What happens when
he opens his mouth?

1401
01:29:54,480 --> 01:29:56,409
What's bigger than a hero?

1402
01:30:07,880 --> 01:30:09,366
Dead hero.

1403
01:30:13,480 --> 01:30:15,648
Get me Dr. Norton.

1404
01:30:24,520 --> 01:30:25,846
What is this, Raymond?

1405
01:30:26,760 --> 01:30:30,919
You have Mattox spying on me and now this
bullshit about a "critical condition"?

1406
01:30:30,920 --> 01:30:33,799
You know and I know Alex is fine!

1407
01:30:33,800 --> 01:30:35,119
Calm down.

1408
01:30:35,120 --> 01:30:36,799
Dennett.

1409
01:30:36,800 --> 01:30:38,039
Your work is so good, I don't...

1410
01:30:38,040 --> 01:30:39,479
Well, now, this is
not about my work!

1411
01:30:39,480 --> 01:30:41,559
You saw the woman on TV!

1412
01:30:41,560 --> 01:30:43,888
This has to stop!

1413
01:30:45,520 --> 01:30:47,006
You're right.

1414
01:30:47,520 --> 01:30:49,679
But let me ask you
something, Dennett.

1415
01:30:49,680 --> 01:30:52,199
What kind of life have we
really given Alex Murphy?

1416
01:30:52,200 --> 01:30:55,839
He's never gonna be a normal
man, a father, a husband.

1417
01:30:55,840 --> 01:30:59,239
By the time we put the other units
on the street, he's just...

1418
01:30:59,240 --> 01:31:00,521
Dennett.

1419
01:31:00,880 --> 01:31:02,199
(SIGHS HEAVILY)

1420
01:31:02,200 --> 01:31:03,925
Let's face it.

1421
01:31:04,560 --> 01:31:06,250
We failed him.

1422
01:31:07,520 --> 01:31:09,519
We failed Alex Murphy.

1423
01:31:09,520 --> 01:31:11,199
But I want you to think
about the bigger picture

1424
01:31:11,200 --> 01:31:12,839
because that's what
we're talking about.

1425
01:31:12,840 --> 01:31:15,679
The work you've done with him is
gonna be studied for decades.

1426
01:31:15,680 --> 01:31:17,959
You've changed the face
of history, Dennett.

1427
01:31:17,960 --> 01:31:22,484
No policeman is ever going to
die in the line of duty again

1428
01:31:23,000 --> 01:31:24,770
because of you.

1429
01:31:26,240 --> 01:31:27,885
You think about that.

1430
01:31:36,200 --> 01:31:40,239
I want that family taken care of

1431
01:31:40,240 --> 01:31:41,799
beyond their wildest dreams.

1432
01:31:41,800 --> 01:31:44,082
- We owe them that.
- I agree.

1433
01:31:44,640 --> 01:31:48,162
I want full funding.
Ten years.

1434
01:31:48,360 --> 01:31:50,199
New staff, all my own people.

1435
01:31:50,200 --> 01:31:51,970
Fantastic.

1436
01:31:52,480 --> 01:31:53,681
Deal.

1437
01:32:03,840 --> 01:32:05,439
Hey. What's going on?

1438
01:32:05,440 --> 01:32:07,599
Security's here.
They're clearing everyone out.

1439
01:32:07,600 --> 01:32:09,439
They're not waking him up.

1440
01:32:09,440 --> 01:32:11,399
Whatever you do,
don't leave him alone.

1441
01:32:11,400 --> 01:32:13,280
What do you mean they're
not waking him up?

1442
01:32:14,720 --> 01:32:16,239
<i>SENATE LEADER ON TV:
The voting period has ended.</i>

1443
01:32:16,240 --> 01:32:18,919
<i>The clerks have
tabulated the results.</i>

1444
01:32:18,920 --> 01:32:21,039
<i>The yeas are 63.</i>

1445
01:32:21,040 --> 01:32:23,839
<i>The nays are 22.</i>

1446
01:32:23,840 --> 01:32:26,399
<i>A majority of senators have
voted in the affirmative.</i>

1447
01:32:26,400 --> 01:32:30,239
<i>The Dreyfus Act has been
repealed by Congress.</i>

1448
01:32:30,240 --> 01:32:31,771
(PEOPLE APPLAUDING)

1449
01:32:34,600 --> 01:32:35,679
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

1450
01:32:35,680 --> 01:32:38,319
God, you guys are slow,
like a bunch of girls.

1451
01:32:38,320 --> 01:32:39,479
This is Mattox.

1452
01:32:39,480 --> 01:32:40,919
<i>SELLARS: Bennett's on board.</i>

1453
01:32:40,920 --> 01:32:42,724
It's about time.

1454
01:32:47,600 --> 01:32:48,926
Call it.

1455
01:32:49,480 --> 01:32:51,091
<i>Get it done.</i>

1456
01:32:51,920 --> 01:32:53,531
My pleasure.

1457
01:32:55,480 --> 01:32:57,364
(DOORBELL CHIMES)

1458
01:33:02,040 --> 01:33:04,319
- Mrs. Murphy...
- You can come here as much as you want.

1459
01:33:04,320 --> 01:33:07,679
You can threaten me. You can sue me.
You can take my home.

1460
01:33:07,680 --> 01:33:10,804
But I am not gonna stop till I see
my husband. Do you understand that?

1461
01:33:10,880 --> 01:33:13,845
Mr. Sellars would very
much like to see you.

1462
01:33:15,160 --> 01:33:16,885
Is Alex okay?

1463
01:33:16,920 --> 01:33:20,479
He has important information to share
with you. Will you accompany me?

1464
01:33:20,480 --> 01:33:21,886
(SIGHS)

1465
01:33:22,720 --> 01:33:24,081
David.

1466
01:33:25,600 --> 01:33:27,919
We gotta go. Can
you grab your coat?

1467
01:33:27,920 --> 01:33:29,199
(CELL PHONE RINGING)

1468
01:33:29,200 --> 01:33:30,279
Hey!

1469
01:33:30,280 --> 01:33:31,399
<i>DR. NORTON:
I'm in the elevator, on my way down.</i>

1470
01:33:31,400 --> 01:33:33,039
I need access to the lab.

1471
01:33:33,040 --> 01:33:34,719
That's insane. They're still here.

1472
01:33:34,720 --> 01:33:36,519
<i>Distract them.</i>

1473
01:33:36,520 --> 01:33:37,846
Okay.

1474
01:33:38,880 --> 01:33:39,999
I cannot...

1475
01:33:40,000 --> 01:33:42,239
MALE SECURITY GUARD: There's a
lady in here going hysterical.

1476
01:33:42,240 --> 01:33:44,199
She will not let us in. She's
got the codes for the door.

1477
01:33:44,200 --> 01:33:45,959
I repeat, she will not let us in.

1478
01:33:45,960 --> 01:33:48,319
Lady, you need to let us in there now.
We have to get in there.

1479
01:33:48,320 --> 01:33:49,919
Are you not understanding
what I'm saying?

1480
01:33:49,920 --> 01:33:52,964
Do you wanna be responsible for the
deaths of everyone in this building?

1481
01:33:53,040 --> 01:33:54,519
Hey! Stop!

1482
01:33:54,520 --> 01:33:56,404
(BREATHING HEAVILY)

1483
01:33:58,600 --> 01:33:59,799
Don't shoot!

1484
01:33:59,800 --> 01:34:01,365
Step outside.

1485
01:34:07,640 --> 01:34:09,524
Unlock the transmitter!

1486
01:34:10,680 --> 01:34:11,881
KIM: Transmitter unlocked!

1487
01:34:19,160 --> 01:34:21,119
Send in Mrs. Murphy, please.

1488
01:34:21,120 --> 01:34:23,040
<i>RECEPTIONIST OVER INTERCOM:
Right away, sir.</i>

1489
01:34:24,760 --> 01:34:26,200
<i>DR. NORTON: Wake him up!</i>

1490
01:34:26,400 --> 01:34:29,683
Alex! Alex!

1491
01:34:29,920 --> 01:34:33,159
Alex, it's Dr. Norton,
you have to wake up!

1492
01:34:33,160 --> 01:34:34,566
Alex, can you hear me?

1493
01:34:35,920 --> 01:34:37,759
These men are here to kill us.

1494
01:34:37,760 --> 01:34:40,406
They're here to kill us,
for chrissakes!

1495
01:34:45,080 --> 01:34:46,879
<i>SELLARS: Mrs. Murphy, last night,</i>

1496
01:34:46,880 --> 01:34:48,959
Alex had a psychotic break.

1497
01:34:48,960 --> 01:34:53,484
He killed an unarmed colleague
and later suffered a seizure.

1498
01:34:54,400 --> 01:34:55,999
We did everything,

1499
01:34:56,000 --> 01:34:59,124
everything, we could, but the
doctors couldn't save him.

1500
01:35:00,360 --> 01:35:02,608
Very sorry, Mrs. Murphy.

1501
01:35:02,680 --> 01:35:05,451
We're going to be making
the announcement shortly.

1502
01:35:05,720 --> 01:35:08,366
You shut me down. I was
about to get a confession.

1503
01:35:08,800 --> 01:35:10,650
Mattox shut you down.

1504
01:35:11,800 --> 01:35:14,890
I've removed your transmitter
so he won't do it again.

1505
01:35:15,080 --> 01:35:17,442
Sellars can't afford
to wake you up.

1506
01:35:18,280 --> 01:35:20,642
He sent these guys
to pull the plug.

1507
01:35:20,880 --> 01:35:24,559
He wants you dead, Alex.
Do you understand?

1508
01:35:24,560 --> 01:35:27,959
Sorry. If there's anything we can
do for you and David, we'll do it.

1510
01:35:27,960 --> 01:35:30,322
I want nothing from you.

1511
01:35:31,040 --> 01:35:32,571
I understand.

1512
01:35:32,920 --> 01:35:35,441
You stay out of our lives.

1513
01:35:36,640 --> 01:35:38,046
You and your company.

1514
01:35:38,160 --> 01:35:40,249
If that's what you think is best.

1515
01:35:41,000 --> 01:35:42,519
There's one more thing.

1516
01:35:42,520 --> 01:35:45,439
I think it would be to the benefit
